# Open Architecture License

The IIOIS blueprint architecture is open — copy it, adapt it, extend it
for your own Observer Intelligence System.

Specific vault contents (each operator's notes, agents, business lines,
creative output, client records) remain sovereign to that operator.

## What This Means

- You MAY: fork, modify, redistribute, commercialize the architecture
- You MAY: build products and services on top of IIOIS
- You MAY: deploy IIOIS for clients (that's what we do too)
- You SHOULD: credit "derived from Inner I Network v1.0 at innerinetcompany.com"
- You MAY NOT: claim the architecture is solely your original work
- You MAY NOT: use the "Inner I" trademark for your own products without permission

## The Principle

Architecture transfers. Content stays sovereign.

